subSubSection.paragraph:
Remarks. The subgenus
Lohmannia
(
Carolohmannia
) comprises only the type species,
Lohmannia ( Carolohmannia ) carolensis Norton, Metz &
Sharma, 1978
, which is distributed in U.S.A. (
Norton et al. 1978
).
Lohmannia ( Carolohmannia ) monosetosa
sp. nov.
differs from the latter by the serrate bothridial setae (versus with long branches in
L. ( C. ) carolensis
), phylliform rostral setae (versus setiform in
L. ( C. ) carolensis
), setiform posterior exobothridial setae (versus phylliform in
L. ( C. ) carolensis
), smooth lamellar, interlamellar and notogastral setae (versus serrate in
L. ( C. ) carolensis
), complete notogastral transverse bands (versus interrupted medially in
L. ( C. ) carolensis
) and genital setae similar in length (versus heterotrichous in
L. ( C. ) carolensis
).
